SINGING LESSONS £60 hour

**First Session £10! **

- West End credited performer with 4 University degrees in teaching and voice and music. YOUR LIE IN APRIL, FROZEN, CYRANO DE BERGERAC, EVITA, THE KING AND I.

-Teaching in London out of Dance Attic Studios Fulham Broadway @danceatticstudios and ONLINE.

- Got recurring technical problems? Have you ever been told that certain genres and songs are just not for you? That your voice will always be a certain way? Have you ever left a singing lesson confused?

- Join the hundreds who have deliberately and conscientiously tackled their technique, and start building confidence today.

- Clients tend to have graduated from 3 year programs and leave with fundamental holes in their technique that they now want to fill. Is that you?

BOOK at www.chrisfung.co.uk

Chris Fung - Singing Teacher

sharedPost.text:
**It's 1974 - Florence Cooper is the agent of aspiring young film actress Daisy White working on the NEW Horror flic - ****‘Fanghelsing’****. **

Florence is a woman making waves as a creditable talent agent in the movie industry. She gets the parts for her clients that no-one understands how… not averse to a bit of bribery, shenanigans or other activities to get what she wants. 

`Screaming Blue Murder' is Alternate Shadows weekend special Murder Mystery - performing at  **Sheerness Golf Club** on 

Sat 1st November - 7.00pm.

Reserve your ticket - Tickets are just £5 and can be obtained by calling the golf club on 01795 662585

sharedPost.text:
✨ A Smile for Christmas – A song that brings warmth and a smile.
When the world outside is wrapped in snow, the pan flute tells of that special moment when a simple smile means more than any gift.
Gentle tones that touch the heart – a musical light in the quiet, festive season.

A song that reminds us: Christmas doesn’t begin under the tree, but in a sincere smile. 🎄😊

A Smile for Christmas – Ein Lied, das Wärme und ein lächeln schenkt.
Wenn draußen die Welt in Schnee gehüllt ist, erzählt die Panflöte von jenem besonderen Moment, in dem ein einfaches Lächeln mehr bedeutet als jedes Geschenk.
Sanfte Klänge, die das Herz berühren – ein musikalisches Licht in der stillen, festlichen Zeit.

Ein Song, der daran erinnert: Weihnachten beginnt nicht unter dem Baum, sondern in einem ehrlichen Lächeln. 🎄😊

Composer : Pan Hope (Horst Peter Zoll)
Artist : PAN HOPE #musik #christmastime #newmusic

items.text:
# Casting Call: German-Speaking Content Creators (Tech)

We’re a tech brand looking for fluent (native-level) German creators to film simple scripted UGC videos.

**What you’ll do**
* Shoot 2–3 short videos following our provided script (total time on set: ~2–3 hours).
* Self-shoot at home or on location with clean light and clear audio.
* Deliver fast — we move quickly.

**You have**
* Native or near-native German.
* Proven self-shooting experience (UGC, reels, ads, or similar).
* A good camera setup (modern smartphone or mirrorless), tripod, and basic audio.
* Reliable turnaround.

**Compensation**
* From **$150** (TBD based on scope and deliverables).

**What we provide**
* Script + shot list
* Creative notes and framing/safe-zone guidelines

**How to apply**

**Marzysz o tworzeniu niezapomnianych historii na scenie i ekranie?**
Dołącz do **Szkoły Reżyserii Teatralnej i Filmowej** – miejsca, gdzie pasja spotyka się z praktyką!

🎭 Ostatni moment rekrutacji – zostało tylko **kilka wolnych miejsc!**
Zajęcia startują już w **listopadzie 2025**.
Weekendowy, dziewięciomiesięczny program zakończony dyplomem – realizujesz własny spektakl i uczysz się pracy z aktorem, scenografem i choreografem.

📩 Nie zwlekaj – twórz, reżyseruj, inspiruj!

sharedPost.text:
We're currently casting an international actor (age 25–36) for the main role of a short film shooting between November 2–3 in Warsaw.

The story is a black comedy about David, an immigrant spending his first christmas in another country with his girlfriend's family. 

❗️Requirements: Must know another language than polish and english, must communicate well in english aswell.

This is a non-profit project, but catering and transport are provided, along with a valuable creative experience in audiovisual storytelling.

If you're interested or know someone who might be, feel free to message me for more details. Looking forward to collaborating! 

🫶🏻For contact my email is : ikateon7@gmail.com

🎬 **SOS STATISZTÁKAT KERESÜNK!** 🎬

Egy **videokliphez** keresünk különböző karaktereket statisztaszerepekre.

📅 **Forgatás:** október 31. (napközben, pontos idősávok egyeztetés alatt)

📍 **Helyszín:** Budapest (13. kerület / Csepel környéke)

⸻

🔹 **KERESÜNK:**

👧 **gyerek statisztákat**

 • 10–16 éves fiúk és lányok

🎬 Jelenet: iskolai ebédlő

⏰ Forgatási idő: kb. 2–3 óra

💰 Díjazás: 15.000 Ft / fő

🧔 **Hajléktalan férfi**

🎬 Rövid utcai jelenet

⏰ 2 óra

💰 Díjazás: 15.000 Ft / fő

👊 **fiatal srácok (18–20 éves)**

🎬 Bullying jelenet – a két főszereplőt megtámadják az utcán

⏰ 2 óra

💰 Díjazás: 15.000 Ft / fő

💃 **fiatal lányok (18–25 éves)**

🎬 Ruhabolti jelenet – a két főszereplő meglesi őket öltözés közben (**fehérneműs jelenet**)

⏰ 2 óra

💰 Díjazás: 25.000 Ft / fő

🚶‍♀️🚶‍♂️ **járókelők (25–55 éves)**

🎬 Utcai jelenet, vegyes karakterek

⏰ Egész nap

💰 Díjazás: 20.000 Ft / fő

👩‍🦳 **idősebb hölgy – ruhabolti eladó**

⏰ 2 óra

💰 Díjazás: 15.000 Ft / fő

🧔 **viccesebb karakterű férfi (40–50 éves) – biztonsági őr**

⏰ 2 óra

💰 Díjazás: 15.000 Ft / fő

Jelentkezni az alábbi linken tudtok:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScAgXYOLXGok01RBkEHOPvxRNKdh2kG-bPJJsuMjxZwbZY8UA/viewform?usp=sharing&ouid=110731860520130588441

**Fontos:** A jelentkezések számára való tekintettel **csak a potenciális jelöltekkel vesszük fel a kapcsolatot.** Köszönjük a megértést! 

Várjuk a jelentkezésed! 📩

message.text:
🎭 ¿Te imaginás actuar, reír y crear… en español, en pleno Budapest?
Entonces este es tu lugar.

Formá parte del primer grupo hispano de teatro en Budapest

No hace falta experiencia: solo ganas de aprender y disfrutar

✅ Clases dinámicas y grupales
✅ Ideal para ganar confianza, soltar el cuerpo y mejorar el idioma
✅ Un espacio cálido, creativo y 100% en español

📍 CASA VEHU — Böszörményi út 4, 1126, Budapest
🗓️ Lunes y miércoles
⏰ 19:00 a 22:00 hs

#casavehu #teatroenespañol #teatro #español #budapest #comunidadhispana #stanislavski

items.text:
Poruszający, mroczny i pełen humoru spektakl teatru cieni na podstawie komiksu Guillaume’a Bianco. Dla wszystkich, którzy mają (lub kiedyś mieli) 10 lat i więcej.

🗓️  2 listopada godz. 12:00

🎟️ Bilety i więcej informacji 👉 https://teatrfigur.pl/repertuar/
Na spektakl należy zakupić bilety zarówno dla dziecka jak również dla opiekuna.

Mówią na niego Mglisty Billy. Lubi samotność, noc, deszcz i melan­cholię. Uwielbia robić draństwa swojej młodszej siostrze Jane i topić mrówki w czekoladowej ślinie. Nie jest niedobry, „po prostu ma charakter”. I ma pewien dar – dar ciemnowidzenia. Kiedyś miał też kota Tarzana, był jego najlepszym przyjacielem, ale pewnego dnia znalazł go zesztywniałego w ogrodzie. Co się dzieje z kocią duszą po śmierci? A przede wszystkim – co to jest śmierć? I czy wszyscy musimy tam iść?

sharedPost.text:
WEZWANIE DO REBELII DUSZY
UNDERGROUND – NIEPOWTARZALNA, ARTYSTYCZNA INICJATYWA

📅 29 listopada 2025 | ⏰ 20:00 – 5:00 | 📍 tajna lokalizacja, Centrum Warszawy

We wschodzącym mroku Warszawy powstaje świat, który istnieje tylko tej jednej nocy. Świat pełen archetypów, rytmu, tajemnicy i magii. Szukamy odważnych dusz, które nie boją się zabłysnąć swoją aurą, charyzmą i wolnością w obliczu publiczności.

Twoim zadaniem będzie prowadzenie narracji, sprawienie, by uczestnicy poczuli, że wkroczyli w surrealistyczny, imersyjny świat stworzony specjalnie na to wydarzenie.
Nie liczy się tylko gra – liczy się sposób bycia, energia, lekkość umysłu i obecność.

Czego szukamy:
 • osób odważnych, pewnych siebie, komunikatywnych i pełnych charyzmy, alternatywnych 
 • umiejętności miękkich i otwartości,
 • poczucia rytmu, tanecznej ekspresji lub wrażliwości na muzykę.

20 miejsc – role do obsadzenia:
 • 5 osób – główne role (królowe, magowie, błazny i inne archetypy)
 • 5 osób – role poboczne
 • 10 osób – mikroakcje, detale tworzące magię wydarzenia

Forma:
 • LARP-owe scenki i role
 • Lekka choreografia, sentencje do zapamiętania
 • System operacyjny prowadzący aktorów 
 • Nie każdy musi być obecny całą noc – zależy od roli

Tematyka:
JAŹŃ, PODŚWIADOMOŚĆ, CIEŃ, NIGREDO, ALBEDO, CITRINITAS, RUBEDO
💠 Ryby i błazen – kluczowe symbole

Zaangażowanie:
 • Pełne poświęcenie i dyskrecja – to świat, który istnieje tylko dla wtajemniczonych
 • Dyspozycyjność w dniach prób (pierwsze spotkanie 10 listopada, stopniowa intensyfikacja)

To pierwszy happening z serii, wyjątkowy w skali Polski i świata. W ramach projektu rozwojowego – traktuj udział jako rozmowę o przyszłej współpracy, potencjalne skalowanie wydarzenia i budowanie portfolio wyjątkowych doświadczeń artystycznych.

Jak zgłosić swoją duszę:
Wyślij maila na: lenamarszalramud@gmail.com
Zawartość zgłoszenia:
 1. Nagranie wideo – opowiedz o swoich pasjach i sposobie radzenia sobie z emocjami (tych jasnych i ciemnych)
 2. Numer telefonu
 3. Dyspozycyjność
 4. Krótka notka o artystycznym ukierunkowaniu: gust, hobby, edukacja

📅 Termin nadsyłania zgłoszeń: 4–5 listopada 2025

Przygotuj się na noc, która zmienia perspektywę, na przestrzeń, w której granice między rzeczywistością a wyobraźnią zacierają się, a każdy krok i gest ma znaczenie.

items.text:
Hi everyone! I have an UNPAID casting and crew opportunity in Hatfield, Hertfordshire.

The production name is 'All That We Feared'.

I'm looking for a male actor for the main role of 'Arlo Jones'

Applicants must be 16+. Playing age of around 17-21. There are no physical requirements for this role.

I'm also seeking for:

-Someone to do sound, own equipment preferably but not required. 

-Lighting, please note this will take place outside with no access to plugs. For this crew role you'll need your own equipment.

-AC, with knowledge of the following; how to pull focus, swapping lenses and general handling.

This production will be taking place on the 2nd November, 3rd November and 1 more date in November that hasn't been decided yet but will likely take place on a weekend.

This project is unpaid. Travel and accommodation are sadly not able to be covered but food and drink will be provided of course. 

This project is perfect for people who are eager to get experience and be on set. To the people who may have an issue with these terms for filming, I completely understand but sadly they are non-negotiable.

To those interested please send me an email ASAP on rdawsonproductions@outlook.com

Hope you've all had/will have an amazing day, thank you!

items.text:
🎬 CASTING NOW – Male Lead for Short Period Drama

We’re urgently casting for Ed Morris, the lead role in The Stuntman — a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol on 11th & 12th November 2025. This is a student production (unpaid, with travel expenses covered) and will be shown at our university showcase and submitted to film festivals.

Story: Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. Determined to save his livelihood, he stages one final ambitious stunt — a warm yet bittersweet story about passion, creativity, and the struggle against inevitable change.

Role: Ed Morris (Lead, 28) Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but quietly desperate as he clings to his dream of preserving silent cinema. Must have strong screen presence and emotional depth.

🎥 Self-tape deadline: Thursday 30th October
💻 Zoom recalls: Friday 31st October
📍 Filming: 11th & 12th November (Bristol area)

To apply, please send your headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

We're currently casting an international actor (age 25–36) for the main role of a short film shooting between November 2–3 in Warsaw.

The story is a black comedy about David, an immigrant spending his first christmas in another country with his girlfriend's family. 

❗️Requirements: Must know another language than polish and english, must communicate well in english aswell.

This is a non-profit project, but catering and transport are provided, along with a valuable creative experience in audiovisual storytelling.

If you're interested or know someone who might be, feel free to message me for more details. Looking forward to collaborating! 

🫶🏻For contact my email is : ikateon7@gmail.com

**NOW CASTING:** LA-based actors for an exciting Amazon campaign highlighting small businesses! 

**Rate:** $**1,200** ($500/12 hr day, $500 buy out, $200 fitting) 

**Usage:** Inperp/worldwide 

Small business owners are natural visionaries, and with Amazon’s support, those big dreams can become reality. We are looking for actors who can represent a few different industries within small businesses that Amazon helps support. 

**Role 1**: Male, age 30-40, small speaking part 

**Role 2**: Female, late 30’s-early 40’s, small speaking part 

**Role 3:** Male, age 25-30 

Please submit a selftape (no more than 30 seconds) to lsteinberg@attn.com introducing yourself and reading the lines designated to each role (LINES BELOW):

**ROLES 1 & 2**: Our company offers free skills training that can help hourly employees level up into higher paying roles. New skills mean more opportunities for the future.
**ROLE 3**: Hey guys. Come with me while I unbox a couple things that just arrived in the mail. This is my first time seeing these items so I’m just as curious as you are for whats inside.** **

items.text:
Casting call for a new series! 

Location: Studio City
Dates: Between November 16-19 (one day; most likely only needed for a few hours) 

We’re assembling a passionate and talented cast for the first shoot of a new original series. This project is being produced for social media distribution but filmed in a horizontal, cinematic format before post-production edits. These initial shoot days will serve as a proof of concept — designed to build audience traction and secure brand partnerships and sponsorship funding for future episodes. These two roles will evolve into regular paid opportunities for our core crew. 

Compensation:
$125 per day, copy, on-set meals (lunch + crafty), and hands-on experience with a full professional production crew — including cameras, lighting, and sound equipment. This is a great opportunity to expand your portfolio with high-quality material.

To Apply:
Please email partnerships@aurelianscollective.com with your headshot and resume/reel and we will send you the sides
 to tape. Thank you for your interest — we look forward to hearing from you!

https://m.imdb.com/title/tt38714186/

items.text:
**SKUESPILLERWORKSHOP med fokus på MONOLOGER:** Jeg har forberedt undervisningen så deltagere, der enten søger ind på skolerne eller som skal audition, kan medbringe sin egen monolog og komme godt ind i sit materiale, så man kan arbejde målrettet frem til prøverne. Der kommer derudover også masser af skuespilteknik og træning, som er værdifuld for både nye og øvede spillere. 

**Hvis du ikke søger ind eller har din egen monolog med**, så har jeg et udvalg af monologer, som jeg sender sammen med velkomstmailen, så snart du er meldt til. Her vælger du en monolog, som du synes, er spændende at arbejde med.

**Og som en lille bonus **skal vi også i fællesskab prøve at arbejde med en monolog skrevet af William Shakespeare. Der er ingen forventninger til at du kender eller kan spille Shakespeare. 

Deltagergebyret er 1475kr. og det foregår d. 1. & 2. november, kl. 10.00 - 15.00 i København

**Skriv til mig mail@michellebercon.com**

items.text:
Warszawa

Szukam na plan reklamy osób do następujących ról!

Modni pracownicy biurowi

Mężczyźni z sali konferencyjnej

fotografowie

widzowie i na wybiegu

fashionistek w dniu lokalizacji

fashionistki w dniu studyjnym.

zdjęcia między 25-27.11 czyli trzeba być dostępnym we wszystkie dni, oraz należy być otwartym na wzięcie udziału w każdej z funkcji bo nieznane są sceny w jaki dni będą grane.

Termin odległy więc proszę o zgłaszanie się osób dyspozycyjnych.

Stawka 200 zł- płatne przelewem.

Proszę zgadzać się na adres mailowy-m.paziewska@stars-impresariat.pl

W tytule proszę wpisać 25-27.11 reklama.

W mailu proszę umieścić- imię, nazwisko wiek tel oraz wyraźne zdjęcia.

Marta 😀😀

items.text:
SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Red, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother’s new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Red see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Red. 

Wanted: 2 actors (1 x M, 1 x F) for exciting new short film ‘In His Care’. Shooting in Hertfordshire, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- RED (Female, 24 – 30)

- Description: Mid to late 20s

Red is a simple, reserved girl. She is kind and holds herself highly. But when it comes to her grandma, she is extremely protective, fierce even. She is perceptive and head strong and will do anything to find what’s happening at grandma’s house.

- Height: 5’5 – 5’9

- Appearance: Red is a modest girl. She dresses simple when visiting her grandmother, always wearing the infamous red scarf that her grandmother gave her.

- Pay Category: travel expenses and food covered

- HARRY (Male, 35 - 50)

- Description: Mid 30s to 50

Harry is carer to Ruth, conniving and manipulative; calculated and dominating. He knows what he wants and how to get it. He isn’t a smart perpetrator but rather simple-minded praying on those who can’t defend themselves and has no one to defend them. He has been getting away with it until a young girl with a fiery soul starts to uncover his secret.

Height: Tall (6ft approx.)

- Appearance: Harry is a seemingly ordinary guy on the outside. Charismatic, confident, tall, handsome, well kept. If you walked past him down the street, he may smile or wink at you. He uses his looks and caring façade as leverage.

- Pay category: travel expenses and food covered

If you’re interested, please submit showreels and any enquiries to sheldonkieran4@gmail.com by 7th November

items.text:
We’re putting together a crew for a comedy series proof-of-concept! It’s like if The Mindy Project, Chewing Gum, and New Girl all had delusional love child! 

We’re hoping to build a creative dream team—a film family we can create with long-term. Once this project is crowdfunded, crew members who join now will be prioritized for the pilot (which will be paid) and the full series 🤞🏽

We need:
• 1st AD
• DP
• 1st AC
• Sound Mixer / Boom Op
• Gaffer
• Script Supervisor
• PA
• PA + BTS

Would love to also connect with:
• Sound Designer 
• Editor
• Composer
• Music Supervisor

Dates: January 30th – February 1st, 2026 (2-3 day shoot)
Location: West LA / Ventura
Compensation: Unpaid (Passion Project) — meals + credit provided

Please submit to Hiring@flyingjewelfilms.com with:

• The position(s) you’re interested in

• A little about you, your experience, and your availability

•  Portfolio, reel ( links/examples of past work), or any other relevant materials

Thank you!!

Follow us on Instagram @flyingjewelfilms for future crew calls and production updates.'

items.text:
My University film course and I are creating a “Surrealist, Psychological” Film Called STUCK

It is written by Daniel TJ Clarke

And Directed by Samuel Preston. 

The Film is about a disillusioned young man, overwhelmed by financial strain and self-doubt, becomes physically and psychologically trapped in his family home. As he navigates surreal and shifting realities, he’s forced to confront uncomfortable truths about privilege, purpose, and the cost of success.

We are in DIRE need of 8-15 extras between the ages of 20-40 years old who are able to travel to University of Winchester’s Business School (At the West Downs Accomodation) on Thursday the 13th of November at 1pm! 

Because we are university students, we will unfortunately not be able to make this a paid experience, however, we are more than happy to accommodate food and drinks, as well as help pay for travel!

Please DM me on Facbook Messenger PR email me on my email that’s on the Poster!

THEN BE AN EXTRA!!! 8-15 extras required Filming on Thursday 13th Novcmber 1-6pm Location: University of Winchester Business School Shakespeare Room 001 Contact z.hussein. tz.busein.23@unimail.vinchesterac. 23@unimail. winchester.ac.uk if you are interested!'

items.text:
**MED FOKUS PÅ KRIG & PREPPING**

**SØGES: Unge på SU til filmoptagelse i København**

Er du mellem 18 og 30 år og på SU?
Vi søger deltagere til en optagelse i et mørkt studie, hvor du sammen med andre unge skal tage stilling til spørgsmål om frygt, forberedelse og fremtid. Du placerer dig fysisk i rummet ud fra, hvor enig eller uenig du er i forskellige udsagn.

Formålet er at undersøge, hvordan unge i dag forholder sig til kriser, samfund og fremtid — ærligt og visuelt.

**Optagelse:** ca. 1 time en eftermiddag i november
**Lokation:** København
**Deltagere:** 10 unge (18–30 år, på SU)

Vi søger en blandet gruppe med forskellige uddannelser og baggrunde. Du behøver ingen erfaring foran kameraet – kun lyst til at deltage i en åben og ærlig samtale.

Send en kort besked med:
• Navn og alder
• Din uddannelse
• Et par linjer om, hvorfor du har lyst til at deltage

Send til lenenydahl@hotmail.com – skriv *GEN PREP –*i emnefeltet.

Tripple D Agency is looking for Male Afrikaans speaking cast members for a telenovela filming in Cape Town.

**PAID**! - **DOCUMENTARY FILM **( LONDON BASED 🇬🇧 ) 
We're seeking Black, South Asian & East Asian participants **aged 18-25 **for a documentary film on identity and representation. This independent documentary explores identity, culture, and belonging through the personal stories of people of colour in the UK. This film aims to shed light on navigating creative dreams, family expectations, and self-expression in modern Britain.

Please get in touch! 🙌 🎬

Razem z przyjaciółką prowadzimy kanał na TikToku (prawie 700 tys. obserwujących) i planujemy nakręcić krótką serię – sześć odcinków po 30–40 sekund – w formie humorystycznego serialu kryminalnego, parodii typowych scen i bohaterów z tego typu produkcji. Chcemy, żeby całość miała charakterystyczny klimat „warszawskiego brudu ulicy” co też jest klasyczne dla Polskich seriali kryminalnych. 
Dodamy też, że byłoby super jakby operator posiadał auto, aby można było komfortowo zmieniać lokalizację. Temat płatności też oczywiście dogadamy. 

Jeśli ktoś byłaby zainteresowany prosimy o zostawanie kom, a się odezwiemy :)))

items.text:
** ⊹ ࣪ **CASTING CALL**⊹ ࣪ ˖**

We are casting for 'Muddy Waters'! 

Please read through the details & character descriptions and send us your audition, or share with people who might be interested!

UBC Student Thesis Short Film

Non-Union, Unpaid/Volunteer (crafty provided)

**Location**: Metro Vancouver

**Shoot Dates:** February 6-8th, 2026

**Logline:** Set in the 90s— Jeannie, an anomalous young adult, unearths an unexpected connection with a marsh creature when she and her friends cast a spell for revenge.

**Genre:** Fantasy, Drama with comedic/camp tones.

**Themes:** Identity, Gender Envy, Found Family, Belonging, Angst.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit a **SELF-TAPE** and/or **DEMO REEL** along with your **HEADSHOT** to [muddywatersfilm@gmail.com](mailto:muddywatersfilm@gmail.com).

Please include your **NAME, HEIGHT, LOCATION**, the** ROLE(s)** you are auditioning for, and confirm that you are **ABOVE THE AGE OF 18**. Acting Resume is optional.

Please submit by **NOVEMBER 3rd**.

*Self-Tape/Demo Reel submissions will still be accepted until December but talent may miss out on in-person audition/chemistry read opportunities if submitted at a later date.*

‧₊˚ ⏾. ⋅

Please note that this is a queer film. Absolutely ZERO hate or discrimination will be tolerated. We will be casting self-identifying queer individuals for all of the queer characters. Even for non-queer characters, we will only be working with talent who are, at the very least, allies in agreement to make the production a safe space. We will also NOT be asking anyone to “prove” their identities to us. What you choose to share with us regarding your gender identity and/or sexuality is entirely up to you. We simply urge talent to audition for the roles that both speak most to them and feel most appropriate. 

Thank you so much! We look forward to hearing from you!

If you have any questions, email us or message us on Instagram:

[muddywatersfilm@gmail.com](mailto:muddywatersfilm@gmail.com)

Follow us on Instagram for updates: @/muddywatersfilm

 ⊹ ࣪ ﹏⏾﹏⊹ ࣪ ˖

sharedPost.text:
🌀🌀🎥🏆Highly advanced acting course on.line

---

🎬 Unlock the Mind, Unlock the Scene

Ever wondered why some performances hit you right in the gut, while others just float by? It’s not luck — it’s psychology, philosophy, and instinct.

In my course, we go deep into the human mind:

Freud → Understand the hidden drives, inner conflicts, and desires that shape your character.

Jung → Explore archetypes, shadows, and the collective patterns that give your role mythic resonance.

Nietzsche → Learn to embrace struggle, chaos, and life itself, transforming it into raw energy for your performance.

This isn’t abstract theory — it’s practical, on-set knowledge:

Build characters that feel alive, complex, and unforgettable.

Hit the emotional beats instinctively.

Turn tension, darkness, and chaos into performance gold.

Whether you’re in front of the camera or behind it, these tools take your craft to another level.

💥 Your mind is your stage — let’s train it to perform.
LONG VERSION 🌀1 to 1 on ZOOM,intensive,acting workshop.helping to push your emotions to the edge.leading to a powerful "sizzle"reel and possible employment on the 8 features I am shooting this year and next..long version.

Including "river talks"produced by "little pig films"

🌀🎬🎥🌚 Exclusive 1-on-1 Acting Workshop

🔥 Limited-Time Offer – Only a Few Spots Left! 🔥
(📩 Message Now to Secure Yours!)

"Imagine walking into an audition with unshakable confidence, delivering a performance so raw and real that the director can't look away."

This isn’t just another acting class. It’s an intensive experience designed to break barriers and elevate your craft.

---

🎭 What Makes This Course Different?

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

Along with working with, Freud, Yung,and Nietzsche..to understand "subtext and archetypes".

🎬 Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

🌍 International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

📽 IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

📽 Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

🎬 Exclusive Opportunity – A Direct Path to Real Work!

At the end of the course, each student will create a high-impact “sizzle reel”, showcasing their strongest performance moments.

🔹 This reel will be personally passed on to the directors of the next 7 feature films I am working on as cinematographer.

🔹 That means real exposure—real opportunities—real chances for work.

🎭 "This isn’t just training. This is your shot to be seen by directors actively casting for upcoming projects."

---

🤔 What You Will Learn:

🌀 Emotional Range – Master a full spectrum of emotions for believable, compelling performances.

🌀 Character Development – Create rich, multidimensional characters with depth and 
realism.

🌀 Method Acting – Use personal experiences to deliver raw, authentic performances.

🌀 Working with Directors & Crew – Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate effectively.

🌀 Scene Preparation – Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

🌀 Industry Standards – Create a professional showreel and understand how to stand out to casting directors.

---

🎬 These Courses Are One-on-One with the Mentor/Director, Who Will Push You to Make the Performance Believable.

---

🎬 Course Breakdown

Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski’s Approach)

🔹 Breaking a Scene Down: Internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

🔹 Character Exercise: The Hitman’s First Kill

📍 Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter’s midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed—a brand-new sniper rifle.(You will be encouraged to "visualize"this)

💥 "Actors I've trained have gone on to land real roles—this course gives you what drama schools miss."

🔹 Exercise 1: Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target.

🔹 Exercise 2: Explore multiple emotional shifts (relief, doubt, fascination, decision).

🌀You have entered the room you are safe (singular emotion)

🌀You see the gun on the bed,the awareness of your reality sinks in.

🌀You make a descion to approach the gun 

🌀You pick up the gun,initially you are captivated by the mastery of it,s creation (momentarily distracting you from the reality of what you are about to do.)

🌀You make the descion to kill(remember in this excercise this is a 1st time "hit person"..why do you make that descion?(Covered in class).

🌀You move to the window,practical ,Now you have decided action will take place.

Explore why using stanislavski techniques,of breaking a scene into ,moment by moment.

It is more fascinating to watch.on screen,the audience does not know "what is going on in your head"..but it is fascinated to watch,and it captures your audience.

🔹 Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set.

🌀:(monologue)an actor,s ability to memorize lines is important .

🎬:in the style of "the late great heath ledger of "Batman dark knights"(a crazed man sits with a portable nuclear bomb,on his lap):

🌀"So you imagine chaos was created in a day?(Sinister,sarcastic)(Pause/breath)"do you think e equals m squared (slow word by word,as if talking to a child),means we can travel back in time?(Smiles,and cricks his/her neck),no it just means we can build an atom bomb!!,and blow things up!(Smiles and claps hands gleefully),we are all going to die (bows as if on stage),and just by chance we,ll remember why.(Pause)...we even did this?,looks at camera slowly . reflectivity,or just perhaps...mmm I don,t know "nobody cares"!!!!!!.

Lifts button to camera and presses it!!!!..

Boom!!!(Note my last student took the entire session to make this believable).

End scene.🎬🎬

---

Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

🔹 Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character’s mind.research I had a director friend who contacted "Liam neelson"to understand him
Heath ledger locked himself in a hotel room
The actor from the "machinenist"almost starved himself to death.

🔹 Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

📍 Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated—until suddenly, you’re holding an AK-47. (Scenes can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)you open fire!!!.

Bang bang bang.
The feeling of power and saying 
F......you all.

Is almost zen like just firing the gun,every round as it falls to the ground is an expression of the rage of anger you feel about ,been born, having to survive,having to make a living,for this day and this day only!(You know for sure the police will kill you)

But this is your day!!!

I will direct you for this scene.

To make it believable

You will have to use "method"and the ability to "source"that"inner rage(which we all have).
To make the scene believable.

Shown to directors I know ..I imagine (if done right,they will be "blown away")

🔹 Alternative Scene: A Joker-like monologue before detonation.

I have script from this scene we can work with.
But it explores "chaos/anarchist"concepts (as expressed by the joker (heath ledger )In "Batman dark knights"

🔹 Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most—desperately trying to convince them not to leave.

The point of this scene (if you choose it)is to make your performance totally believable.

🎭 "Imagine the tension of a final phone call—the stakes couldn’t be higher. This is where real acting happens."

🔹 Accents: British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents for performance versatility.

🔹 Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness – convey pure serenity in front of the camera.

The American Indians used to say "a camera steal,s your soul"

A film camera can almost "see inside you"
The purpose of this course is to help you create that "believability"and emotion.

---

Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

🔹 Understanding your role in the filmmaking process.

🔹 Technical skills: hitting marks, lighting awareness, and camera shooting ratios.
If you don,t appreciate what your crew does,and are say arrogant,well does not make for a nice shoot?

Most actor,s I have worked with are empathetic,kind and understanding 
🔹 Collaborating with crew—continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

📽 Final Showreel Scenes:

🎭 Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it?" You imagine that your karma was not noted,your actions had no consequences.

🎭 Heartbroken: "But I didn’t mean it... please, don’t leave me…I know now that without you I could never imagine how my life would be"

🎭 Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc², then time versus chaos... Means excistance is just a theory ,I have this bomb..the one thing Einstein /Oppenheimer manager to create..so bye bye..let,s push the button!!

🎭 Flat & Emotionless: "We’re born, we live, we die. That’s it." If heaven exists,and we are re.born with "conciseness ",then heaven would become like hell,
As "time"and a sense of time ,knowing we are going one day ,gives us ..in way (deep pause look to camera)a security.

---

Day 4: Fear and Survival – Personal Experience & Character Creation

🔹 Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

🔹 Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape
📍 Scene: You’re lost in the jungle at night. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out—pleading for help. No answer.

🎭 Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death – the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation – the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion – feeling your body give in.

🔹 Exercise 2: The Final Phone Call Redux
📍 Scene: You’re on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it’s over.

🎭 "This isn’t just acting—it’s about reaching deep into your own experiences to find truth in the performance."

------

🎬:Session 5: Unlocking the Inner World — Freud, Jung, and Nietzsche in Action

 🚨A short script will be given:

🎥:."Sometimes I just can,t feel my self inside,it,s as if something is missing ,but ..I can,t quite put my finger on it"

Jung ,Freud and Nietzsche will be discussed in class...there different philosophies on life .

Perform the script 3 times with those different subtexts in mind.

---

Objective:

To integrate the psychological and philosophical concepts we've explored (Freud's hidden desires, Jung's archetypes, and Nietzsche's self-empowerment) into a character's internal journey, enhancing the depth of performance and pushing actors toward more complex, dynamic roles.

---

🚨1. Understanding the Inner Conflict (Freud)

Exercise:
Guide your actors to explore a hidden desire or repressed emotion within their character that contradicts their outward behavior.
Example: An actor playing a “stoic” hero could uncover a deep fear of abandonment they are trying to repress, which sneaks through in moments of weakness.(Script will be given)

🌀Goal:
Reveal the complexity of a character by exploring subconscious drives and how they create inner conflict in their actions.

---

🚨2. Finding the Archetypes (Jung)

🌀Exercise:
Ask your actors to identify which archetype (Hero, Shadow, Wise Old Man, Rebel, etc.) their character is embodying in the scene.
Then, have them break the archetype — let them experiment with how the character could act outside their usual role to reveal something deeper about their personal growth.(Script will be given)

🌀Goal:
Explore how different archetypes influence a character’s actions and how those archetypes evolve through the story.

---

🚨3. Creating the Übermensch Moment (Nietzsche)

🌀Exercise:
Have your actors play out a moment where their character faces a crucible—a choice that pushes them beyond their old self and forces them to create their own values.
Example: A character might choose self-sacrifice to uphold their personal code, even though it risks everything (script will be given)

Goal:
Challenge the actor to play moments of personal transformation, where their character is creating their own power in the face of destruction or moral ambiguity.

---

🌀4. Integration and Performance

Exercise:
Give your actors a scene where all three elements come into play:

Freud's inner conflict (hidden desires or repressions)

Jung's archetypes (the character wearing multiple masks)

Nietzsche’s self-empowerment (the character breaking free and reimagining their world)
Guide them to play the scene with all these layers, digging into the internal battle, archetypal masks, and the potential for self-transformation.(Script will be given).

Goal:
Combine these psychological and philosophical elements to create a rich, multi-dimensional character.

---

Wrap-Up:

Discuss how each character’s internal journey was shaped by their hidden emotions, their spiritual archetypes, and their search for power.

Reflect on how they can continue to explore their characters’ deeper layers in future roles.

🎬 Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they’ve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

💥 Their best moments will be compiled into a high-impact sizzle reel—directly sent to directors casting for upcoming feature films.
That I am either producing or about to be cinematographer on.

---

🎬🎥 Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

🔥 For Less Than the Price of a Casting Workshop, You Get 1-on-1 Coaching and a Real Chance for Work!

📢 LIMITED SPOTS AVAILABLE – MESSAGE NOW TO SECURE YOUR PLACE!

📩 DM or Email: mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let’s create something unforgettable.
---

---

Mike Muschamp’s Philosophy Map – The Big Five

1️⃣ Freud – The Mind’s Hidden Drives

Core idea: Unconscious desires and fears shape behavior.

Use in acting/storytelling: Know why characters (and people) do what they do. Subtle gestures, hesitation, tension = meaningful.

2️⃣ Jung – Archetypes & Shadows

Core idea: Universal patterns, archetypes, and the hidden “shadow” influence life.

Use in acting/storytelling: Tap into archetypes to make characters mythic; explore shadow for emotional depth.

3️⃣ Nietzsche – Will to Power & Self-Overcoming

Core idea: Life is chaos; create your own meaning and values.

Use in acting/storytelling: Turn struggle into strength, show transformation, act boldly.

4️⃣ Camus – Absurdity & Joy in Struggle

Core idea: Life has no inherent meaning; joy comes from living fully despite it.

Use in acting/storytelling: Embrace absurdity in scenes, add existential tension and truth.

5️⃣ Viktor Frankl (“Frank”) – Meaning in Suffering

Core idea: Even in suffering, humans can find purpose; choosing your attitude = freedom.

Use in acting/storytelling: Transform hardship into performance, purpose, and inspiration.

---

How They Mix Together – Your Signature Lens

Freud + Jung: Understand inner drives and archetypal patterns.

Nietzsche + Camus: Embrace chaos, self-overcome, find joy in struggle.

Frank: Give all of it purpose; turn learning and life into meaning.

Result: A philosophical toolkit that powers acting, directing, writing, and living

✨ Ihr exklusives Shooting 2025 – Erinnerungen, die bleiben ✨
📸 Zwei Wunsch-Themen. Ein Profi-Team. Unvergessliche Bilder.

Ob für ihre Familie, ihren Partner, für sie selbst, ihr Business-Profil oder für eine Modelmappe:
Ein professionelles Shooting ist mehr als nur Fotos. Es ist ein Erlebnis, das man spürt… und dann natürlich auch sieht!

Michael Diehl ist renommierter Fotograf aus Esslingen mit jahrzehntelanger Erfahrung in seinem stylischen Studio oder auf Location, mit dem Blick für das Besondere und der Gabe, jede Persönlichkeit zum Strahlen zu bringen.

Dinah Zahran ist BeautyCreator Visagistin mit Feingefühl und Meisterhand. Sie hat das Auge fürs Detail und ein Gespür dafür, das Beste in ihnen hervorzuheben. Sie schminkt und stylt die Haare typgerecht und passend zum Outfit. Sie sorgt dafür, dass sie sich wohl, schön und authentisch fühlen.

Zusammen sind sie ein eingespieltes Team und schaffen eine Atmosphäre, in der sie sich fallen lassen können: entspannt, herzlich und voller Energie.
Keine steifen Posen, kein künstliches Lächeln, dafür echte Momente und viel gute Laune.

📅 Termine – limitierte Plätze:
14.–16. November 2025 (Fr–So)
21.–23. November 2025 (Fr–So)
Slots: 10–12 Uhr | 13–15 Uhr | 16–18 Uhr
(Nur 18 Plätze – wenn weg, dann weg.)

💄 Das erwartet Sie:
- Typgerechtes Hair & Make-up (ca. 45 min) von Dinah
- 1-2 Stunden Shooting mit 2 Wunsch-Themen ihrer Wahl
- Hochauflösende Bilder ohne Wasserzeichen (Farbe, getont oder s/w)
- Professionelle Bearbeitung von je 1 Bild pro Thema nach Wahl
- Alle Nutzungsrechte für private & geschäftliche Eigenpräsentation (Social Media, LinkedIn, Xing, Modelagenturen etc.)
- Das Styling mit entsprechender Mode sind ihre Lieblingsoutfits aus ihrem Kleiderschrank. Auf Wunsch helfen wir ihnen im Studio dann gerne bei der entsprechenden Zusammenstellung.

🎁 Perfekt als Weihnachtsgeschenk:
Für sie selbst, für ihren Lieblingsmenschen, für ihren Business-Headshot, ihre Fashion- oder Beauty-Porträts, für ihr Modelbook oder einfach nur was schönes und sinnliches unterm Weihnachtsbaum – alles ist möglich.

Auch als Gutschein bis 23.12.25 verfügbar.

💰 Preis:
Alles inklusive: 450 € zzgl. MwSt.

📩 Buchung:
Schreiben sie einfach eine PN oder WhatsApp, um ihren Wunschtermin zu sichern.
Studio-Preview: [https://lnkd.in/gtVy_vN7](https://lnkd.in/gtVy_vN7)
Mehr Eindrücke: [www.mdiehl-photography.com](http://www.mdiehl-photography.com) & @[beautycreator.de](http://beautycreator.de)

✨ Lache, posiere, sei du selbst – Michael und Dinah fangen die Momente ein, die bleiben.

LONDON BASED ONLY (or willing to travel once a month).

Acting Now Creatives is a brand new coop talent agency with one lead agent in London open to representing British and International talent based in LONDON in film/TV/commercials (we don't do theatre).

We are not only seeking actors but also creators/actors who create or want to develop their writing and creative skills.

We not only offer representation but also free showreel production and occasional short films with our clients. That's where you'll be able to develop your creative skills.

On top of that, we only take 10% commission.

- Available to shoot from the 10th - 15th November or 17th - 22nd November 2025?

***Wees op VIA!***

sharedPost.text:
Equity North London branch would like to encourage neurodivergent actors to please get in touch and share their challenges and struggles with the self taping audition process.

It has become apparent that lack of clear instructions, or even conflicting instructions (particularly in commercial castings, though not limited to this area) for filming and completing self tapes is problematic for a lot of actors but that it is also, in some cases, a barrier to neurodivergent actors being able to complete and submit auditions.

Actors should not have to miss out on opportunities for these reasons, nor should they have to highlight their neurodivergence/disability to obtain clarification and understanding when it is not relevant to the role for which they are applying. 

We would like to hear your experiences and challenges with self taping to get a better outline of where neurodivergent actors are struggling so that we can put a plan in motion to try to work together with agents and casting directors to improve and clarify the process and thus make self taping more inclusive.

Diversity and inclusivity for all disabilities in our industry is important and so we want to hear your voices so that we can work together make things better for neurodivergent actors.

Please get in touch with Lydia to share your experiences here: okaysocial@outlook.com

Hi folks! Looking for subjects to participate in a social experiment for CBC's Marketplace.

Unpaid/Volunteer but costs covered.

We're looking for people and families who have food affordability at the top of their mind to participate in an on-camera food challenge. 

Shooting dates throughout November...flexible & remote.

Please email jenny.cowley@cbc.ca if you're interested, and include where you're located, a bit about you and/or your family, why food affordability is at the top of your mind, and steps you've taken to save money on food costs.

Personal Student Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTRESSES FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20–23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment “META MONTAGE”

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he’s writing, reality and fiction intertwine — forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20–23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Student short film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JUDY (20s–30s)

As Character, Actor, and Generative AI.

A multi-layered role that shifts between human emotion and digital consciousness.

SOFIA (20s–30s)

Jack’s girlfriend — the emotional axis between love, illusion, and authorship.

Contact:

Director / Writer / Producer : Yuri Kakuya

📧 hkjfilm@gmail.com

Casting call!

We're so excited to be casting for our female-focused feature film, Before Us!

Log line: Five strangers wrestle with motherhood and identity while, unbeknownst to them, their great grandmothers meddle from the afterlife. As their stories increasingly intertwine, the women must discover purpose from within themselves and from one another.

Genre: Dramedy

Paid, non-union

This first casting call includes our leads and key supporting roles, each paying $500-$750 depending on the success of fundraising and the final shooting schedule. We plan to shoot a teaser trailer and some social media content for fundraising purposes in November, with principal photography in January-February 2026. You can see full character breakdowns and audition submission instructions here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mi16s2oN0Gdn0KYzpTw6VKL1LIG1mytkHOXYFYM_a3M/edit?pli=1

We're casting for:

Izzy: 30, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, Izzy can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Agnes: 51, female, Chinese-American (While a Chinese actress is ideal, Agnes can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Sasha: 36, female, Black

Beatrice: Any age 50 or older, female, Black

Leticia: Any age 50 or older, female, Latina

Mabel: Any age 50 or older, female, Chinese (While a Chinese actress is ideal, she can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Manåmko’: Any age 50 or older, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, she can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Margaret: Any age 50 or older, female, white

Foster: 29, male, any ethnicity

Please submit your audition via the form linked above by 11:59 pm on Saturday, November 1.

items.title: Casting call!

items.text:
· Title: This Side of Midnight

· Genre: Horror

· Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

· Role: Lilith — Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera — Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith’s best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad — Male, 40s–50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom — Female, 40s–50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling — Any gender (preferably male), 10–15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier — Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

· Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin — Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange — Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

· Production Type: Student Film

· Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange — escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

· Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

· Compensation: Unpaid

· Union Status: Non-Union

· Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1–2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

· Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

· Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

· Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one’s own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

items.text:
Hello, 
We are looking for two performers to act in a short movie. “Where the Light Shines” explores denial, anxiety, and female identity in a male-dominated society. The film reflects the tension between masculine and feminine energy – control and surrender – and how these forces collide in the face of inner truth.
The story uses contemporary movement and dance to showcase the troubled inner-word of the characters. You will be working closely with the director and choreographer to shape the narrative.
Females, non-binary and all ethnicities is encouraged to apply!<3 This is a third year Bachelor project.  
If you are ready to move with the lights, contact us at: edsh.production@gmail.com.

‼ ‼ ‼  UWAGA ŚLĄSK   #CASTING 🎥‼ 📽‼

Realizujemy krótkometrażowy film fabularny na ŚLĄSKU. To opowieść o osamotnieniu, nieuchronnej utracie i potrzebie więzi w obliczu ginącego świata. Czy gdy wszystko wokół znika, można wciąż zbudować prawdziwe  relacje?

ZDJĘCIA SĄ ZAPLANOWANE W TERMINIE: 30.11.2025 – 06.12.2025 

#Poszukujemy :  ‼ ‼  ‼  AKTORÓW ‼ ‼ ‼      
 
1. AKTORKA - Ekspedientka, wiek ok. 37 lat, raczej szczupła 
2. AKTORKA - Pierwsza sąsiadka, wiek ok.  71 lat, -
                          ‼ ‼ ‼ ORAZ EPIZODYSTÓW    ‼ ‼ ‼ 
3. EPIZOD - Druga sąsiadka, wiek ok. 66 lat 
4. EPIZOD - Nastolatka z psem, wiek ok.  16 lat 
5. EPIZOD - Kobieta z rowerem, wiek ok. 55 lat , raczej szczupła, naturalna, z ciekawą osobowością.
6. EPIZOD - Przechodzień, wiek ok. 45 lat, bez dialogu – 1 dzień 
7. EPIZOD - Starszy mężczyzna, wiek ok. 66 lat, epizod – 1 dzień 

Szukamy ciekawych, prawdziwych twarzy – osób z charakterem, osobowością i autentycznością i życiową prawdą w spojrzeniu. Zależy nam na ludziach, którzy mają w sobie coś wyjątkowego i wiarygodnego. Wiek - nie trzymamy się sztywno wieku – ważniejsze, by osoba dobrze oddawała charakter roli. Nie mamy wymagań co do koloru włosów, wzrostu czy typu urody – najważniejsza jest autentyczność i charyzma.

#Preferujemy zgłoszenia osób mieszkających, przebywających na terenie #Śląska 
#Zlecenie płatne.

‼ ‼ ‼ WAŻNE: KOMPLETNE ZGŁOSZENIE‼ ‼ ‼   zawierające poniższe dane, ➡️➡️wyślij  na adres e-mail 📧: strzelecka.barbara@wp.pl
 ‼ Tytuł e-maila: do której z ról wysyłasz zgłoszenie np. 1. AKTORKA - Ekspedientka, jeśli do dwóch, także proszę podać których.

🏠 Miejsce zamieszkania ..................
📅Wiek ...................
📊Wzrost ........................

+2 aktualne zdjęcia -> portret i sylwetka (bez osób trzecich, bez nakryć głowy i bez okularów przeciwsłonecznych)

Mirek Rygiel (46) – wysoki, całkiem przystojny mężczyzna, choć zniszczony alkoholem. Bezczelny, ma problemy z agresją, pewny siebie, potrafi podobać się kobietom, ale to przemocowiec.

Data: 12. I 15. listopada

Stawka: 700 zł netto za całość

Chętnych Panów zapraszam do wysyłania zgłoszeń na adres: casting.outset@interia.pl

W tytule maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.

W treści maila proszę o zawarcie następujących informacji:

*Wiek/wzrost/waga

*Nr tel. Do kontaktu

*Krótki opis doświadczenia

*Linki do sowich materiałów video – demo/wizytówka/scenki  castingowe

*Aktualne zdjęcie

Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu/noclegu

sharedPost.text:
Ogłoszenie , nabór do spektaklu teatralnego
                          "Oda do Perforacji."
                                       🎭    
   
  Centrum Praw Kobiet we Wrocławiu oraz reżyserka i autorka sztuki poszukują aktorek do nowego spektaklu pt. " Oda do perforacji", którego premiera jest planowana na koniec lutego 2026 r.
    
  Sztuka porusza doświadczenia kobiet, które przeżyły przemoc - fizyczną, psychiczną, ekonomiczną czy instytucjonalną. Nie jest to jednak dokument - to poetycki, symboliczny i przejmujący głos oddany kobietom, które odzyskały sprawczość i własny język. 
 
Szukamy kobiet z Wroclaw [Wroclove] i okolic, w różnym wieku i z różnym doświadczeniem scenicznym( mile widziane zarówno osoby z doświadczeniem, jak i debiutantki).  

Szukamy aktorek do ról głównych i epizodycznych, osób otwartych na pracę z trudnym materiałem, ale w bezpiecznych warunkach twórczych. Próby odbywają się we Wrocławiu w siedzibie Centrum Praw Kobiet pod opieką reżyserki i psychologa , obecnego na całym etapie procesu twórczego. 
  
Zapewniamy profesjonalne przygotowanie artystyczne, przestrzeń do współtworzenia znaczącego spektaklu, szacunek dla granic i osobistych historii każdej osoby biorącej udział w procesie.

Zgłoszenia przyjmujemy do 3 grudnia 2025 roku.
Telefon kontaktowy 729 372 280 - Sara 🎭 

❗Projekt realizowany w ramach wolontariatu ❗

(LIVE/In person open call auditions)

Date: Saturday 11/01/25 (November 1, 2025) and 11/2/25 (November 2, 2025

Time: 9am 

Location: K75 STUNT ACADEMY 13560 49th St N Suite 10, Clearwater, FL 33762

 

VUONA Entertainment is seeking experienced stunt performers for overseas contracts in China

​

Male 5’6” and above (170cm+) and Female 5’5” and above (165cm+) stunt performers of all ethnicities, ages 18+

Must be proficient in at least one of the following:

Fight choreography / screen combat

High falls

Fire burns

Wire work

Vehicle or motorcycle stunts

Acrobatics / parkour

Water or underwater stunts

Specialty skills (jet-ski, high divers, etc)

 

REQUIREMENTS:

1. Current stunt headshot, resume and demo reel (can be sent to k75stuntacademy@gmail.com, subject STUNT SHOW)

2. Must be physically fit, safety-conscious, and able to follow direction

3. Flexible and comfortable working in various weather and terrain conditions.

Day of Audition will consist of:

1. Pull ups

2. Cardio

3. Agility

4. Mat work: front and back, dive rolls, cartwheels, etc

5. Fight Choreography

6. Type-outs throughout audition 

Please bring printed headshot and resume to audition. 

Please bring your hydration, towel and running shoes 

No weapons allowed (prop or otherwise)

No work boots or sandals allowed 

No food allowed inside gym

Vuona at K75 Auditions form:

https://forms.gle/GibBXWPAu4xYfY198

Thank you 

#Stunts #Stunt #China #Choreography #Fire #Action

items.text:
🎬 **PAID CASTING CALL – Faith-Based Short Film** 🎬
Multiple age ranges needed!
Inspired by an ancient story of courage and faith – see full details below 👇

**Production Type:** Short Film (Faith-Based / Biblical Origin)
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Location:** Filming in the U.S.
**Compensation:** Paid (rate TBD)
**Dates:** TBD – currently gathering cast

**SEEKING TALENT (All Roles):**
* Females: **12–13**, **18–19**
* Males: **12–13**, **18–19**, **35–45**, **45–55**
*(All roles call for darker or Middle Eastern features to authentically reflect the time period and setting.)*

**About the Project:**
A powerful short film inspired by an ancient, faith-based story. We’re looking for expressive and grounded actors who can bring sincerity, emotion, and strength to the screen.

🎞 **Audition Details:**
Auditions will be **self-taped.**
Script sides will be provided **after initial email submission.**

📸 Please include in your email:
* A clear, recent headshot or photo
* Resume (if available)
* A short intro video (name, age, location, and a few sentences about yourself)

📧 **TO SUBMIT:**
Email**: madison@capture-films.com**
Subject line: 👉 **“Your Name – Short Film Submission”**

sharedPost.text:
CASTING CALL — Feature Film: DELTA PROTOCOL

We are now casting for the upcoming feature film Delta Protocol, the follow-up to Buying Time — now streaming on Amazon Prime, Tubi, and other major VOD platforms.

Story Summary:
Set around the year 2030, Delta Protocol follows Daniel and Tess, who find themselves trapped in a dangerous web of betrayal and manipulation. As they fight to uncover the truth, they risk everything to expose a conspiracy that could tear their world apart.

About the Production:
Delta Protocol is being Produced and Directed by Kris Smith and Andy Blithe, an experienced filmmaking duo with over half a dozen feature films between them — including Buying Time (2024) and Diamond Dogs (2025). This will be their most ambitious project yet, planned to shoot in 2026 in small production blocks.
This is a micro-budget, profit-share production.

At this stage, there is no budget for cast or crew expenses, as all available funds will go towards essential costs such as food and locations. However, all contributors will receive a profit share if the film generates revenue through VOD platforms or other channels, based on their role and involvement.

Casting Details:
We are looking for a range of talent — from main roles and supporting characters to background artists.
Filming will take place in and around Norwich and surrounding areas.

How to Apply:
Please email the following to office@aturn.co.uk:
Your name and contact details
Your approximate playing age
A recent photograph
A showreel or Spotlight link (if available)

Selected applicants will be matched to potential roles and invited to submit a self-tape audition from a short script extract.
We aim to respond to all applicants.

items.summary: Hi all. I’m 21 from London (although i dont look it in this video i need a haircut). I took my first acting class on Saturday which is helpful and I’m currently exploring acting. I made a self tape based on a play called Black Boys who have considered suicide when the hue gets too heavy. I had to condense it but it still really long. Just wanted some honest thoughts on it. Thanks

items.text:
BOOKS OPEN - coop agency approved by Spotlight.
LONDON BASED ONLY (or willing to travel once a month).

Acting Now Creatives is a brand new coop talent agency with one lead agent in London open to representing British and International talent based in LONDON in film/TV/commercials (we don't do theatre).

We are not only seeking actors but also creators/actors who create or want to develop their writing and creative skills.

We not only offer representation but also free showreel production and occasional short films with our clients. That's where you'll be able to develop your creative skills.

On top of that, we only take 10% commission.
No fees!

We are looking for professional actors/creators who are responsible, high standards of writing and communication skills, and quick to respond to emails, as most self-tapes are last minute.

More information:
www.ancagency.co.uk/join

#acting #actors #actorslife #talentagent #seekingrepresentation  #booksopen

CASTING CALL  ☆ GAINESVILLE, FL  ☆ SHORT FILM  ☆ MEAL AND IMDB CREDIT PROVIDED  ☆ ACTORS OF ALL AGES, GENDERS AND EXPERIENCE LEVELS ☆

Step right up folks, casting for Funny Bones has just begun! 

Funny Bones is an independent short film that will be filmed in Gainesville, FL between Saturday, November 22nd through Tuesday, November 25th. Unpaid and non-union, but IMDB credit and hot meals will be provided. 

Roles we are searching for include:

☆ WENDY (female-presenting, 20s, major supporting): Suave magician and Mimi the clown’s best friend. Confident and successful.

☆ MIKE "MIKEY" MOUSSE (male-presenting, 40s, major supporting): Slimeball party agency owner with a thick Jersey accent. All about the bottom line.

☆ LALA (female-presenting, 20s, major supporting): Clown and ringleader of an underground speakeasy performance troupe. Empathetic and caring.

☆ CLOWN NURSE/DR. CLOWN (any gender, late 20s-70s, supporting): A clown who is both a nurse and a doctor.

☆ AUNT MARIE (female-presenting, 30s-40s, supporting): Uptight mime who can’t stand those who deviate from tradition. Conservative and uppity. *NOT A SPOKEN ROLE. AUDITION MUST BE MIMED*

☆ BIRTHDAY KID (any gender, ages 6-12, supporting): Excited child celebrating their 10th birthday.

We are seeking actors of all ages, genders, and experience levels to be apart of this project! Submissions are open NOW through Sunday, November 2nd at 11:59PM! 

AUDITION HERE: [https://forms.gle/znH6WzVN7t6KZwwq5](https://forms.gle/znH6WzVN7t6KZwwq5)

READ SIDES HERE: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1sjb4XDpZdkCCJ2KQasJIDq0-XvFEKPon?usp=drive_link

Please feel free to message me with any questions! Thank you!

casting call 🚨

As a part of a school application I need to shoot a 3 minute bit.

The project will be about the exciting meeting of 2 friends outside of the prison one of them was in for two years.

I’m looking for a male actor who’d be taking the role of the friend who’s being released from jail, ideally mid - late 20’s, dark short hair (if someone here has a buzz cut that would be freakin amazing 😭) 

It’s a really low budget project but I’d be happy to give a small symbolic payment to a talented actor who’d be engaged in telling our story 💗

# **🎥 Casting Call! **

​

Wir suchen vier Darsteller:innen für einen Messefilm in Düsseldorf!

Gedreht wird am 17. & 18. November auf der Messe Düsseldorf sowie an weiteren Terminen im November an passenden Locations.

​

Hier alle Rollen im Überblick:

​

👨 Arzt / Ärztin (40–55 Jahre)

Seriös, sympathisch und authentisch.

Dein zusätzlicher Drehtag ist am 14. November.

​

👩 Frau mit Migrationshintergrund / Start-up-Darstellerin (30–35 Jahre)

Modern, kommunikativ und selbstbewusst.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 5. November – kurzer Vorab-Dreh.

​

👩 Pflegekraft (25–35 Jahre)

Einfühlsam, natürlich und offen.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

👨‍🔬 Forscher:in / Wissenschaftsbereich (30–40 Jahre)

Professionell, ruhig und fokussiert.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

📍 Drehorte: Messe Düsseldorf + thematisch passende Arbeitsumgebungen

📅 Drehtage: 5., 14., 17., 18., 22. oder 29. November (je nach Rolle)

💶 Gage: 300 € pro Drehtag → insgesamt 900 € pro Person

​

Wenn du Lust auf ein professionelles, sympathisches Team und eine spannende Produktion hast, kommentiere einfach „Info“ 👇

​

Dann schicken wir dir den Bewerbungslink mit allen weiteren Details!

👩 Pflegekraft (25–35 Jahre)

Einfühlsam, natürlich und offen.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

👨‍🔬 Forscher:in / Wissenschaftsbereich (30–40 Jahre)

Professionell, ruhig und fokussiert.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

📍 Drehorte: Messe Düsseldorf + thematisch passende Arbeitsumgebungen

📅 Drehtage: 5., 14., 17., 18., 22. oder 29. November (je nach Rolle)

💶 Gage: 300 € pro Drehtag → insgesamt 900 € pro Person

​

Wenn du Lust auf ein professionelles, sympathisches Team und eine spannende Produktion hast, kommentiere einfach „Info“ 👇

​

Dann schicken wir dir den Bewerbungslink mit allen weiteren Details!

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 44/2025

DER KOBOLD MIT DEM ROTEN HAAR IST ZURÜCK UND RUNDES JUBILÄUM EINES KULTKLASSIKERS

Vor 2 Jahren feierte der Pumuckl ein fulminantes Comeback nach 40 Jahren. Ab morgen sorgt er erneut in den Kinos für allerlei Schabernack. 

Die Film Dokumentation Girls & Gods läuft aktuell in den Kinos. Mit den beiden Regisseuren Arash T. Riahi und Verena Soltiz durften wir ein Interview machen.

Vor 50 Jahren feierte die ROCKY HORROR PICTURE SHOW ihre Kinopremiere. Der Film galt anfangs als Flop. Doch durch Longruns in den damaligen Programmkinos avancierte der Streifen zum Erfolg. Passend zum Halloween Weekend bringen das Stadtkino Horn und die Lichtspiele Gföhl den Timewarp zurück auf die Leinwand.

Weitere Filmtipps und Musik aus Filmen der letzten 85 Jahre  präsentiert Ihnen Sarah Fuchs.

Mittwoch 29.10.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

# Statist*innen für neues YouTube-Dating-Format gesucht!

Was sagt der TikTok-Feed über uns aus? Kann man darüber entscheiden, ob man eine Person daten möchte oder nicht?

Für ein neues YouTube-Dating-Format sind wir auf der Suche nach Kandidat*innen und einem Moderator, die herausfinden wollen, wie aussagekräftig der TikTok-Algorithmus für potentielle Dating-Partner*innen ist.

Du schaust gerne TikToks, und du hast kein Problem damit, deinen Feed offenzulegen? Dann bewirb dich als Kandidat*in!

Bewirb dich jetzt als Single – wir bewerten den TikTok Feed gemeinsam, du triffst deine Entscheidung!

Zeitraum: 7. + 8.11. (du musst nur an einem der beiden Drehtage Zeit haben)

Ort: Köln

130 € Aufwandsentschädigung, Reisekostenpauschale nach Absprache

Bewerbungslink: [[https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn](https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn)](https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn)

Bei Fragen, melde dich gerne unter casting@33minutes.de

items.text:
Statister søges i Vejle/Horsens 📹✨

Tidligere optagelser blev aflyst, så jeg søger igen statister til at medvirke i lidt video i Vejle/Horsens fredag den 7. november.

𝗛𝘃𝗲𝗺 𝘀ø𝗴𝗲𝗿 𝗷𝗲𝗴:

Jeg søger to "familier". 

Familie 1: En mand og en kvinde, der kan passe til en børnefamilie. Hertil også en-to børn. 

Familie 2: Et mere "modent" par (mand og kvinde) samt en eventuel hund.

OBS! Ingen store, synlige tatoveringer eller lignende. 

𝗣𝗿𝗮𝗸𝘁𝗶𝘀𝗸 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗼: 
📍 Optagelserne foregår i Vejle eller Horsens.

🗓️ Fredag den 7. november. Enten kl. 9.30-12.00 eller 13.00-15.00. Det aftales nærmere.

💸 Jobbet betales med gavekort på 500 kr. pr mand. 

💌 Send en mail til jdk@miltonhuse.dk med billeder af dig/jer. Henvendelser på Facebook eller andre steder besvares IKKE. 

Obs! Optagelserne skal bruges til annoncering på Metas samt andre digitale platforme til et typehusfirma. Der er tale om flere klip af et hverdagsliv i et af vores udstillingshuse.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**
*Half-Day Social Media Shoot – Housing Association*

 

Hi everyone! 👋

 

We’re an independent media agency, looking for a small group of confident actors to feature in a short **half-day** filming project for a well-known **Housing Association**.

📍 **Location:** Welwyn Garden City

📅 **Date:** ASAP

⏱️ **Duration:** Half-day (approx. 4 hours)

💸 **Usage:** Digital Channels only 

🎥 **Style:** Natural, lifestyle content - showcasing everyday living and community vibes

 

We’re looking for:

✨ A diverse mix of people, ideally aged 30–45

✨ Comfortable on camera, relaxed and authentic energy (not a speaking part)

✨ Able to take light direction and have fun with it!

 

If you’re interested, please **comment below or drop me a message** with:

1️⃣ A recent headshot or link to your profile/portfolio 

2️⃣ Your location / ability to travel

3️⃣ Your availability W/C 3rd November

 

Feel free to tag anyone you think would suit this too! 🙌

 

Thanks so much - looking forward to connecting!

Conrad

items.text:
**CASTING – WORK/LIFE OUTDOORS (Betalt job)**

Vi søger 4–6 personer i alderen 25–50 år til foto- og videooptagelser den 
5.–6. november på Sydsjælland og Møn.

**Optagelserne foregår over to dage:**

Dag 1 (onsdag 5. november): Stevns Klint og Skovtårnet

Dag 2 (torsdag 6. november): Næstved og Møns Klint

**Vi søger dig, der:**
* Er 25–50 år
* Har naturlig karisma og udstråling
* Ser professionel ud, men uden at være for poleret
* Kan agere naturligt i en lille gruppe
* Er frisk på at være ude i naturen (klinter, skov, byrum)

**Påklædning:**

Casual business – pænt, men afslappet.

Lag-på-lag, naturtoner, sneakers, chinos, strik, skjorter. Ingen jakkesæt eller høje hæle.

**Honorar:** 1.000 kr. pr. dag (inkl. transport og forplejning)

**Optagelser:** 5.–6. november 2025

Send 2-3 billeder af dig selv (portræt + fuld figur)

samt et par linjer om dig selv til: nicklas@anvig.com

items.text:
Don’t if someone can help or give me advice 

I’m a actress with autism and learning disabilities 
I been working hard on building on my portfolio and training and recently did training in London 

I have worked with national theatre and royal philharmonic orchestra and had couple of paid screen appearances as an main actor and some credits 

I have a high quality showreel,headshots, cv 

I’m struggling to get into spotlight at the moment 

I have been contacting agents 
And some just don’t get back while others are saying or books are full we can’t take new clients and a few other say we can’t take you on right now but we will you in consideration if your agents are free they take things further. It’s a little confusing for me to understand what that means i thought if they rejecting you they just simply will not  contact you back , 

dont if anyone can help me understand this better for me please 

But I struggling to get an agent that actually want take things further even the inclusive ones ￼￼￼

Much appreciated thank you

# **🎥 Casting Call! **

​

Wir suchen vier Darsteller:innen für einen Messefilm in Düsseldorf!

Gedreht wird am 17. & 18. November auf der Messe Düsseldorf sowie an weiteren Terminen im November an passenden Locations.

​

Hier alle Rollen im Überblick:

​

👨 Arzt / Ärztin (40–55 Jahre)

Seriös, sympathisch und authentisch.

Dein zusätzlicher Drehtag ist am 14. November.

​

👩 Frau mit Migrationshintergrund / Start-up-Darstellerin (30–35 Jahre)

Modern, kommunikativ und selbstbewusst.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 5. November – kurzer Vorab-Dreh.

​

👩 Pflegekraft (25–35 Jahre)

Einfühlsam, natürlich und offen.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

👨‍🔬 Forscher:in / Wissenschaftsbereich (30–40 Jahre)

Professionell, ruhig und fokussiert.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

📍 Drehorte: Messe Düsseldorf + thematisch passende Arbeitsumgebungen

📅 Drehtage: 5., 14., 17., 18., 22. oder 29. November (je nach Rolle)

💶 Gage: 300 € pro Drehtag → insgesamt 900 € pro Person

​

Wenn du Lust auf ein professionelles, sympathisches Team und eine spannende Produktion hast, kommentiere einfach „Info“ 👇

​

Dann schicken wir dir den Bewerbungslink mit allen weiteren Details!

Hello fellow Colorado actors. Many of you may not know that as a SAG member actors need to follow SAG rules. I have seen several violations of SAG rules, not only in our Denver market, but in New Mexico as well. Did you know that SAG rule 14 states:

A member cannot work as both a performer and a casting director, or a performer and a member of another theatrical teamster union, on the same production without the union's consent? 

Actors should not be casting directors due to a conflict of interest, as it can lead to biased decision-making in favor of their own acting career, and because the two roles require different skill sets. 

A casting director's job is to serve the production's needs by finding the best fit for a role, a process that requires a separate and objective perspective from the actor's self-interest in getting cast. 

If you know of anyone that is breaking SAG rule 14, I urge you to call or email SAG in Los Angeles and ask to speak with their violation’s department. You can also make the claim anonymously!￼

SAG-AFTRA / (855) 724-2387
info@sagaftra.org

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'SAG- >SAG-AFTRA hi SAG G.AFTRA'

topComments.text: People are joking, but the lack of professionalism is what's killing the film industry out here. Everyone wants to be the next big thing without the responsibility that entails. There are union rules for a reason
But also remember, narcs go on Santas naughty list. ✊🎅❤️😂

items.text:
HOLDING PATTERN: A film noir by Nico Guin from Denver School of the Arts’ VCA department!
Looking for 3 actors for a 5-minute film-noir!When a wealthy business woman meets a new love interest, she puts him to the test through a private investigator to find out if he can be trusted. 
Roles are not paid or promised.

ESTELLE - The younger wealthy business woman who is in love with John. She wants to test his potential as a love interest, but things take a turn. Estelle is cold, harsh, and confident, while also being sympathetic and unsettling.
JOHN -  John, a younger man who spends whatever money he has at the bar, who has been dating Estelle for a few months and really likes her. Unfortunately, when presented by Victor with the option to steal her fortune in the form of stocks and bonds, he decides the money is too enticing to decline, leading to his ultimate demise. 
VICTOR - The mysterious private investigator hired by Estelle to test whether or not John can be trusted as her future partner. He is ambiguous yet seemingly trustworthy to John, and offers him the job to steal Estelle’s assets.

We will be shooting during the first 3 weekends of November, and are pretty flexible with time of day! 
If you are interested or have any questions, you can reach out to me at 914900@dpsk12.net or 720-255-2717. Thank you!
